@startuml example
title Example deployment diagram (PlantUML escape hatch)

cloud "CDN" as cdn

node "App host" {
  artifact "service" as svc
}

node "Data host" {
  database "primary store" as db
}

cdn --> svc : HTTPS
svc --> db : SQL

note bottom of db
  Replace this starter diagram with your project's actual
  deployment topology. Deployment diagrams are an escape-hatch
  type: Mermaid has no first-class deployment diagram, so this
  file stays PlantUML and is re-rendered by revise via the
  project-declared render command. Common diagram types
  (sequence, class, state, ER, flowchart, light C4) belong as
  fenced mermaid blocks inside the markdown spec files instead.
end note

@enduml
